  nickname: lam
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sorrows of Zion'
      title: The Sorrows of Zion
      number: 1
      content: '    How solitary and lonely sits the city [Jerusalem]That was [once]
        full of people!How like a widow she has become.She who was great among the
        nations!The princess among the provinces,Has become a forced laborer!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She weeps bitterly in the nightAnd her tears are [constantly] on
        her cheeks;Among all her lovers (political allies)She has no one to comfort
        her.All her friends have dealt treacherously with her;They have become her
        enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Judah has gone into exile under afflictionAnd under harsh servitude;She
        dwells among the [pagan] nations,But she has found no rest;All her pursuers
        have overtaken herIn the midst of [her] distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The roads to Zion are in mourningBecause no one comes to the appointed
        feasts.All her gates are desolate;Her priests are groaning,Her virgins are
        grieved and suffering,And she suffers bitterly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Her adversaries have become her masters,Her enemies prosper;For the
        Lord has caused her griefBecause of the multitude of her transgressions;Her
        young children have goneInto captivity before the enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All her beauty and majestyHave departed from the Daughter of Zion
        (Jerusalem).Her princes have become like deerThat have found no pasture;They
        have fled without strengthBefore the pursuer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the days of her affliction and homelessnessJerusalem remembers
        all her precious thingsThat she had from the days of old,When her people
        fell into the hand of the adversary,And no one helped her,The enemy saw her,They
        mocked at her downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jerusalem sinned greatly;Therefore she has become an unclean thing
        [and has been removed].All who honored her [now] despise herBecause they
        have seen her nakedness;Even she herself groans and turns [her face] away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Her (ceremonial) uncleanness was on her skirts;She did not [seriously]
        consider her future.Therefore she has come down [from throne to slavery]
        in an astonishing manner;She has no comforter.\u201CO Lord\u201D [cries Jerusalem],
        \u201Clook at my affliction,For the enemy has magnified himself [in triumph]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The adversary has spread out his handOver all her precious and desirable
        things;For she has seen the [Gentile] nations enter her sanctuary (the Jerusalem
        temple)\u2014  The ones whom You commandedThat they should not enter into
        Your congregation [not even in the outer courts].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All her people groan, seeking bread;They have exchanged their desirable
        and precious things for foodTo restore their lives.\u201CSee, O Lord, and
        considerHow despised and repulsive I have become!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs it nothing to you, all you who pass this way?Look and see
        if there is any pain like my painWhich was severely dealt out to me,Which
        the Lord has inflicted [on me] on the day of His fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From on high He sent fire into my bones,And it prevailed over them.He
        has spread a net for my feet;He has turned me back.He has made me desolate
        and hopelessly miserable,Faint all the day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The yoke of my transgressions is bound;By His hand they are knit
        and woven together.They have come upon my neck.He has made my strength fail;The
        Lord has put me into the handOf those against whom I cannot stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord has rejected all the strong menIn my midst;He has proclaimed
        an established time against meTo crush my young men.The Lord has trampled
        down as in a wine pressThe Virgin Daughter of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I weep for these things;My eyes overflow with tears,Because a comforter,One
        who could restore my soul, is far away from me.My children are desolate and
        perishing,For the enemy has prevailed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zion stretches out her hands,But there is no comforter for her.The
        Lord has commanded concerning JacobThat his neighbors should be his enemies;Jerusalem
        has become a filthy thing [an object of contempt] among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe Lord is righteous and just;For I have rebelled against
        His commandment (His word).Hear now, all you peoples,And look at my pain;My
        virgins and my young menHave gone into captivity.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I [Jerusalem] called to my lovers (political allies), but they deceived
        me.My priests and my elders perished in the cityWhile they looked for food
        to restore their strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'See, O Lord, how distressed I am!My spirit is deeply disturbed;My
        heart is overturned within me and cannot rest,For I have been very rebellious.In
        the street the sword kills and bereaves;In the house there is [famine, disease
        and] death!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'People have heard that I groan,That I have no comforter [in You].All
        my enemies have heard of my desperation;They are delighted [O Lord] that
        You have done it.Oh, that You would bring the day [of judgment] which You
        have proclaimedSo that they will become like me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Let all their wickedness come before You;And deal with them as You
        have dealt with meBecause of all my transgressions;For my groans are many
        and my heart is faint.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Anger over Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Anger over Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '  How the Lord has covered the Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem)With a
        cloud in His anger!He has cast down from heaven to the earthThe glory and
        splendor of IsraelAnd has not remembered His footstoolIn the day of His anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord has swallowed up; He has not sparedAll the country places
        of Jacob.In His wrath He has thrown downThe strongholds of the Daughter of
        Judah (Jerusalem).He has brought them down to the ground [in disgrace];He
        has debased the kingdom and its princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In fierce anger He has cut off and destroyedEvery horn of Israel.He
        has withdrawn His right handFrom the presence of the enemy.And He has burned
        in Jacob like a flaming fireConsuming all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He has bent His bow like an enemy;He has set His right hand like
        an adversaryAnd slain all that were delightful and pleasing to the eye;In
        the tent of the Daughter of ZionHe has poured out His wrath like fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord has become like an enemy;He has swallowed up Israel.He has
        swallowed up all its palaces;He has destroyed its strongholdsAnd multiplied
        in the Daughter of JudahMourning and lamentation (expressions of grief).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And He has violently broken down His temple like a [fragile] garden
        hedge;He has destroyed His appointed meeting place.The Lord has caused the
        appointed feast and SabbathTo be forgotten in ZionAnd has despised and rejected
        the king and the priestIn the indignation of His anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord has rejected His altar;He has abandoned His sanctuary.He
        has given into the hand of the enemyThe walls of her palaces;They have made
        a noise in the house of the LordAs on a day of an appointed feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord determined to lay in ruinsThe [city] wall of the Daughter
        of Zion.He has stretched out a line,He has not stopped His hand from destroying.He
        has caused the rampart and the wall to lament (mourn in grief);They have
        languished together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Her gates have sunk into the ground;He has destroyed and broken her
        bars.Her king and her princes are [exiled] among the nations;The law is no
        more.Also, her prophets no longer findVision from the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The elders of the Daughter of ZionSit on the ground keeping silent;They
        have thrown dust on their heads,They have covered themselves with sackcloth.The
        virgins of JerusalemHave bowed their heads to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My eyes fail because of tears [mourns Jeremiah],My spirit is deeply
        disturbed;My heart is poured out on the earth [in grief]Because of the destruction
        of the daughter of my people [Jerusalem],When little ones and infants faintIn
        the streets of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They cry to their mothers,\u201CWhere is grain and wine?\u201DAs
        they faint like a wounded manIn the streets of the city,As their life [slips
        away and] is poured outIn their mothers\u2019 arms.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'How shall I console you?To what shall I compare you,O Daughter of
        Jerusalem?With what shall I compare you, so that I may comfort you,O Virgin
        Daughter of Zion?For your ruin is as vast as the sea;Who can heal you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your prophets have seen (imagined) for youFalse and foolish visions;And
        they have not exposed your wickednessTo restore you from captivity [by teaching
        you to repent],But they have seen (imagined) and declared to you false and
        misleading oracles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "All who pass along the wayClap their hands in derision at you;They
        scoff and shake their headsAt the Daughter of Jerusalem, saying,\u201CIs
        this the city that was called\u2018The perfection of beauty,The joy of all
        the earth\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "All your enemiesHave opened their mouths wide against you;They [scornfully]
        hiss and gnash their teeth.They say, \u201CWe have swallowed her up!Certainly
        this is the day for which we waited;We have reached it, we have seen it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Lord has done what He planned;He has accomplished His wordWhich
        He commanded from days of old.He has demolished without sparing,And He has
        caused the enemy to rejoice over you;He has exalted the power of your enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Their hearts cried out to the Lord.\u201CO wall of the Daughter of
        Zion,Let your tears run down like a river day and night;Give yourself no
        relief,Let your eyes have no rest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Arise, cry aloud in the night,At the beginning of the night watches;Pour
        out your heart like waterBefore the presence of the Lord;Lift up your hands
        to HimFor the life of your little onesWho are faint from hungerAt the head
        of every street.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'See, O Lord, and look!With whom have You dealt this way?Should women
        eat their offspring,The little ones who were born healthy and beautiful?Should
        priest and prophet be killedIn the sanctuary of the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The young and the oldLie on the ground in the streets;My virgins
        and my young menHave fallen by the sword.You have killed them in the day
        of Your anger,You have slaughtered, not sparing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You [Lord] called as in the day of an appointed feastMy terrors (dangers)
        on every side;And there was no one who escaped or survivedIn the day of the
        Lord\u2019s anger.Those I have cared for and brought up with tenderness,My
        enemy annihilated them."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah Shares Israel\u2019s Affliction"
      title: "Jeremiah Shares Israel\u2019s Affliction"
      number: 1
      content: '  I am [Jeremiah] the man who has seen afflictionBecause of the rod
        of His wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He has led me and made me walkIn darkness and not in light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely He has turned His hand against meRepeatedly all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He has caused my flesh and my skin to waste away;He has shattered
        my bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He has besieged and surrounded me with bitterness and hardship.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He has made me live in dark placesLike those who have long been dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He walled me in so that I cannot get out;He has weighted down my
        chain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Even when I cry out and shout for help,He shuts out my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He has blocked my ways with cut stone;He has made my paths crooked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He is to me like a bear lying in wait,And like a lion [hiding] in
        secret places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has turned aside my ways and torn me in pieces;He has made me
        desolate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He has bent His bowAnd set me as a target for the arrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He has caused the arrows of His quiverTo enter my inner parts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have become the [object of] ridicule to all my people,And [the
        subject of] their mocking song all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He has filled me with bitterness;He has made me drunk with wormwood
        (bitterness).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He has broken my teeth with gravel;He has [covered me with ashes
        and] made me cower in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My soul has been cast far away from peace;I have forgotten happiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Hope of Relief in God\u2019s Mercy"
      title: "Hope of Relief in God\u2019s Mercy"
      number: 18
      content: "So I say, \u201CMy strength has perishedAnd so has my hope and expectation
        from the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Remember [O Lord] my affliction and my wandering, the wormwood and
        the gall (bitterness).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My soul continually remembers themAnd is bowed down within me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But this I call to mind,Therefore I have hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It is because of the Lord\u2019s lovingkindnesses that we are not
        consumed,Because His [tender] compassions never fail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They are new every morning;Great and beyond measure is Your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThe Lord is my portion and my inheritance,\u201D says my soul;\u201CTherefore
        I have hope in Him and wait expectantly for Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The Lord is good to those who wait [confidently] for Him,To those
        who seek Him [on the authority of God\u2019s word].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It is good that one waits quietlyFor the salvation of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'It is good for a man that he should bearThe yoke [of godly discipline]
        in his youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Let him sit alone [in hope] and keep quiet,Because God has laid it
        on him [for his benefit].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Let him put his mouth in the dust [in recognition of his unworthiness];There
        may yet be hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Let him give his cheek to the one who strikes him;Let him be filled
        with reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the Lord will not reject forever,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For if He causes grief,Then He will have compassionAccording to His
        abundant lovingkindness and tender mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'For He does not afflict willingly and from His heartOr grieve the
        children of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To trample and crush under His feetAll the prisoners of the land,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'To deprive a man of justiceIn the presence of the Most High,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "To defraud a man in his lawsuit\u2014The Lord does not approve of
        these things.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Who is there who speaks and it comes to pass,Unless the Lord has
        authorized and commanded it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Is it not from the mouth of the Most HighThat both adversity (misfortune)
        and good (prosperity, happiness) proceed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Why should any living mortal, or any man,Complain [of punishment]
        in view of his sins?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Let us test and examine our ways,And let us return to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Let us lift up our hearts and our hands [in prayer]Toward God in
        heaven;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'We have transgressed and rebelled,You have not pardoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'You have covered Yourself with angerAnd pursued us;You have slain
        [without pity] and have not spared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'You have covered Yourself with a cloudSo that no prayer can pass
        through.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'You have made us scum and refuseAmong the peoples (Gentile nations).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'All our enemies have gaped at us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Panic and pitfall (traps, danger) have come on us,Devastation and
        destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'My eyes overflow with streams of tearsBecause of the destruction
        of the daughter of my people (Jerusalem).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'My eyes overflow unceasingly,Without stopping,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Until the Lord looks downAnd sees from heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'My eyes [see things that] bring pain to my soulBecause of all the
        daughters of my city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Without cause my enemiesHunted me down like a bird;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'They silenced me in the pitAnd placed a stone over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "The waters ran down on my head;I said, \u201CI am cut off (destroyed)!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'I called on Your name, O Lord,Out of the lowest pit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "You have heard my voice,\u201CDo not hide Your ear from my prayer
        for relief,From my cry for help.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "You drew near on the day I called to You;You said, \u201CDo not fear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "O Lord, You have pleaded my soul\u2019s cause [You have guided my
        way and protected me];You have rescued and redeemed my life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'O Lord, You have seen the wrong [done to me];Judge my case.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'You have seen all their vengeance,All their schemes against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'You have heard their reproach, O Lord,And all their schemes against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'The lips and whispering of my assailantsAre against me all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Look at their sitting and their rising [their actions and secret
        counsels];I am their mocking song [the subject of their ridicule].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'You will repay them, O Lord,According to the work of their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'You will harden their hearts;Your curse will be upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: You will pursue them in anger and destroy themFrom under the heavens
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Distress of the Siege Described'
      title: Distress of the Siege Described
      number: 1
      content: '  How dark and dim the gold has become,How the pure gold has changed!The
        sacred stones [of the temple] are poured out and scatteredAt the head of
        every street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The [noble and] precious sons of Zion,[Once] worth their weight in
        fine gold,How they are regarded [merely] as earthen jars,The work of a potter\u2019s
        hands!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even the jackals offer the breast,They nurse their young;But the
        daughter of my people has become cruelLike ostriches in the wilderness [that
        desert their young].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The tongue of the infant clingsTo the roof of its mouth because of
        thirst;The little ones ask for food,But no one gives it to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who feasted on delicaciesAre perishing in the streets;Those
        reared in purple [as nobles]Embrace ash heaps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the [punishment of the] wickedness of the daughter of my people
        [Jerusalem]Is greater than the [punishment for the] sin of Sodom,Which was
        overthrown in a moment,And no hands were turned toward her [to offer help].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Her princes were purer than snow,They were whiter than milk [in appearance];They
        were more ruddy in body than rubies,Their polishing was like lapis lazuli
        (sapphire).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their appearance is [now] blacker than soot [because of the prolonged
        famine];They are not recognized in the streets;Their skin clings to their
        bones;It is withered, and it has become [dry] like wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Those killed with the swordAre more fortunate than those killed with
        hunger;For the hungry pine and ebb away,For the lack of the fruits of the
        field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The hands of compassionate womenBoiled their own children;They became
        food for themBecause of the destruction of the daughter of my people [Judah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Lord has fulfilled His wrath;He has poured out His fierce angerAnd
        has kindled a fire in ZionThat has consumed her foundations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The kings of the earth did not believe,Nor did any of the inhabitants
        of the earth,That the adversary (oppressor) and enemyCould enter the gates
        of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Because of the sins of her [counterfeit] prophetsAnd the wickedness
        of her [unfaithful] priests,Who have shed in her midstThe blood of the just
        and righteous;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They wandered, blind, in the streets;They were defiled with bloodSo
        that no one could touch their garments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "People cried to them, \u201CGo away! Unclean!Depart! Depart! Do not
        touch!\u201DSo they fled, then they wandered [as fugitives];People among
        the nations said,\u201CThey shall not stay here any longer with us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The presence of the Lord scattered them [among the nations];He will
        not continue to look after them.They did not honor the priests;They did not
        favor the elders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '[And as for us,] yet our eyes failed,Looking in vain for help.Watching
        [from the towers] we watchedFor a nation that could not save.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The enemy hunted our steps,So that we could not walk in our streets;Our
        end drew near,Our days were finishedFor our end had come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Our pursuers were swifterThan the eagles of the sky;They pursued
        us on the mountains,They waited in ambush for us in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The breath of our nostrils, the anointed of the Lord [our king],Was
        captured in their snares,He of whom we had said, \u201CUnder his shadowWe
        shall live among the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Rejoice and be glad, O Daughter of Edom,Who lives in the land of
        Uz.But the cup [of the wine of God\u2019s wrath] will pass to you as well;You
        will become drunk and make yourself naked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The punishment of your sin has been completed, O Daughter of Zion;The
        Lord will no longer send you into exile.But He will punish your sin, O Daughter
        of Edom;He will expose your sins.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prayer for Mercy'
      title: A Prayer for Mercy
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, remember what has come upon us;Look, and see our reproach
        (national disgrace)!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers,Our houses to foreigners.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'We have become orphans without a father;Our mothers are like widows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We have to pay for our drinking water;Our wood comes to us at a price.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Our pursuers are at our necks;We are worn out, there is no rest for
        us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We have given the hand [as a pledge of fidelity and submission] to
        Egypt and Assyria to get enough bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Our fathers sinned, and are no more;It is we who have carried their
        sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Servants rule over us;There is no one to rescue us out of their hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We get our bread at the risk of our livesBecause of the sword [of
        the Arabs] in the wilderness [who may attack if we go out to harvest the
        crop].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Our skin is as hot as [the heat of] an ovenBecause of the burning
        heat of [the fever of] famine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They ravished the women in Zion,The virgins in the cities of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Princes were hung by their hands;Elders were not respected.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Young men worked at the grinding mill,And boys fell [staggering]
        under loads of wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Elders are gone from the gate;Young men from their music.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The joy of our hearts has ended;Our dancing has been turned into
        mourning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The crown has fallen from our head [our honor is covered with dust]!Woe
        to us, for we have sinned!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because of this our heart is faint,Because of these things our eyes
        are dim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As for Mount Zion, which lies desolate,Foxes and the jackals prowl
        over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But You, O Lord, reign forever;Your throne endures from generation
        to [all] generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Why do You forget us forever?Why do You forsake us so long?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Return us to You, O Lord, so that we may be restored;Renew our days
        as of old,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Unless You have utterly rejected usAnd are exceedingly angry with
        us.
      comments: []
